From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0022/N] JvmOverrideFiles.gmk: drop -O on frame_aarch64.cpp to avoid Morello clang 17 ICE

Build 27 stopped with a clang internal compiler error (exit 134) in
the AArch64 Instruction Selection pass while compiling
`frame::sender_raw` in `src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/frame_aarch64.cpp`.
The crash is in Morello clang's own backend, not in our source —
the optimizer path triggers an ISel-time assertion under purecap.

Lowering the optimization level to NONE for this one file
sidesteps the buggy pass. The function is short (~17 lines) and
called from `frame::sender(map)` only — losing -O3 here costs
negligible runtime. Re-evaluate when the Cambridge CTSRD team ships
a newer Morello LLVM.

Guard the override by toolchain=clang + target_cpu=aarch64 so
non-CHERI aarch64 + x86 builds are unaffected.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0022)

--- a/make/hotspot/lib/JvmOverrideFiles.gmk
+++ b/make/hotspot/lib/JvmOverrideFiles.gmk
@@ -151,3 +151,12 @@ else ifeq ($(call isTargetOs, windows), true)
   BUILD_LIBJVM_jvmciCompilerToVMInit.cpp_OPTIMIZATION := NONE

 endif
+
+# stopless-java-gc: workaround Morello clang 17 ICE in AArch64 Instruction
+# Selection pass on frame::sender_raw. Bug surface is the optimizer; -O0
+# avoids the crash. Re-evaluate when Cambridge ships a newer Morello LLVM.
+ifeq ($(TOOLCHAIN_TYPE), clang)
+  ifeq ($(OPENJDK_TARGET_CPU), aarch64)
+    BUILD_LIBJVM_frame_aarch64.cpp_OPTIMIZATION := NONE
+  endif
+endif
